};
---

<IndividualPageLayout
    title={seoTitle}
    description={seoDescription}
    schema={pageSchema}
    pageTitle={pageTitle}
    heroImage="/oscar/media/stainless-steel-investment-casting-components-hero.webp"
    heroImageAlt="Titanium investment casting hero image showing a finished precision cast component, ceramic shell tree, and molten metal pouring in a modern foundry"
    faqSectionTitle="Frequently Asked Questions: Stainless Steel Casting"
    faqItems={faqs}
    ctaTitle="Request Quote For Stainless Steel Casting"
    ctaDescription=""
    sourcesTitle="Sources"
    sourcesList={sources}
    resourcesTitle="Our Internal Resources for Die Casting, Investment casting, Forging and Sand Casting"
    resourcesList={internalResources}
>

    <div slot="full-width" class="individual-content">

        <section id="overview" >
            <div class="content-container">
                
                <h2>Stainless Steel Casting: Corrosion-Resistant Precision Manufacturing</h2>

                <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center mt-6">
                    <div>
                        <p>
                           ForceBeyond is a premier global supplier of high-precision stainless steel investment castings. 
                           By utilizing the advanced lost-wax casting process, we manufacture highly intricate, near-net-shape stainless steel components 
                           that deliver exceptional corrosion resistance, heat tolerance, and structural durability.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Operating under a strict ISO 9001:2015 quality management system, our global foundry network provides scalable manufacturing solutions for the world’s 
                            most demanding environments. From sanitary food processing fittings to high-pressure marine valves, we produce fully machined, passivated, 
                            and assembly-ready stainless steel parts weighing from a fraction of an ounce up to 200 pounds.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="relative">
                        <div class="overflow-hidden">
                            <img
                                src="/oscar/media/precision-stainless-steel-investment-casting-parts-4k.webp"
                                alt="Precision stainless steel investment-cast parts with machined flanges, threaded ports, mounting holes, and industrial housing features on a white background."
                                class="w-full h-auto object-cover hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-500"
                            />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="technical-capabilities" >
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Technical Specifications: Stainless Steel Alloys</h2>
                    <p>
                        ForceBeyond pours a comprehensive range of austenitic, martensitic, and precipitation-hardening (PH) stainless steel alloys. 
                        We ensure strict metallurgical control to maximize the specific chemical and mechanical properties required by your application.
                    </p>
                    <div class="content-table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="col">Alloy Grade</th>
                                <th scope="col">Typical Tensile Strength</th>
                                <th scope="col">Typical Yield Strength</th>
                                <th scope="col">Key Features & Optimal Applications</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>

                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">304 / 304L</th>
                                <td>75,000 psi (515 MPa)</td>
                                <td>30,000 psi (205 MPa)</td>
                                <td>The standard "18/8" stainless. Excellent general corrosion resistance and weldability. Ideal for food & dairy equipment, medical instruments, and commercial plumbing.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">316 / 316L</th>
                                <td>70,000 psi (485 MPa)</td>
                                <td>25,000 psi (170 MPa)</td>
                                <td>Contains molybdenum for superior resistance to chloride pitting. The premier choice for marine hardware, chemical processing, and wastewater fluid control.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">17-4 PH</th>
                                <td>Up to 150,000+ psi (Condition H900)</td>
                                <td>Up to 130,000+ psi</td>
                                <td>A precipitation-hardening alloy offering an exceptional combination of high strength, hardness, and corrosion resistance. Used heavily in aerospace, pump shafts, and oil & gas valves.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">410 / 416</th>
                                <td>70,000+ psi (Annealed)</td>
                                <td>40,000+ psi</td>
                                <td>Martensitic stainless steels that can be heat-treated for high hardness and wear resistance. Ideal for industrial cutlery, hand tools, and highly stressed valve parts.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">430</th>
                                <td>65,000 psi (450 MPa)</td>
                                <td>30,000 psi (205 MPa)</td>
                                <td>Ferritic stainless with good corrosion resistance and oxidation resistance at elevated temperatures. Often used in decorative applications and automotive trim.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div> 
                <p>
                    (Note: For applications requiring extreme resistance to stress corrosion cracking and pitting in harsh chloride environments, 
                    explore our dedicated Duplex and Super Duplex Stainless Steel Casting capabilities).
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="why-forcebeyond" >
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Why Partner with ForceBeyond for Stainless Steel Casting?</h2>
                
                <p>
                    Machining stainless steel from solid billet is notoriously difficult, tool-intensive, and wasteful. 
                    Investment casting provides the ultimate solution for complex stainless components.
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Intricate Internal Geometries:</strong>The lost-wax process allows for the creation of complex internal coring, undercuts, and intersecting fluid channels that are impossible or cost-prohibitive to machine from solid steel.
                    <li>
                        <strong>Near-Net-Shape Accuracy:</strong>We achieve extremely tight dimensional tolerances (ISO 8062 CT5 to CT7), drastically reducing the need for secondary CNC machining on work-hardening materials like 304 and 316 stainless.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Superior Surface Finish:</strong>:The fine ceramic shells used in our foundries yield exceptionally smooth as-cast surfaces (125 RMS or better). This significantly reduces the time and cost required for manual polishing in sanitary or decorative applications.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Optimized Material Yield:</strong>Stainless steel and PH alloys are expensive. Investment casting pours metal directly into your final part shape, virtually eliminating material waste and lowering per-part costs on high-volume runs.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id = "Tier-1.5-integration">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Tier-1.5 Integration: Cast-to-Machine Solutions</h2>
                <p>
                    Because stainless steel applications often require strict hygiene or high-pressure sealing, the final finish and dimensional accuracy are critical. 
                    ForceBeyond’s Tier-1.5 model integrates precision casting with comprehensive secondary processing.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>High-Precision CNC Machining:</strong>5-axis milling, turning, and threading of critical sealing faces and mounting datums.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Passivation & Electropolishing:</strong>We utilize advanced chemical passivation to restore the crucial protective chromium-oxide layer after casting and machining. For medical and sanitary parts, we offer premium electropolishing for ultra-smooth, sterile surfaces.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Advanced Heat Treatment:</strong>Solution annealing to maximize corrosion resistance, and specific precipitation age-hardening (e.g., H900, H1150) for 17-4 PH components to lock in required tensile strength.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Rigorous NDT:</strong>100% Radiographic Testing (X-Ray) and Fluorescent Penetrant Inspection (FPI) to guarantee zero internal or surface defects in high-pressure fluid control parts.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="certified-applications" >
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Certified Stainless Steel Applications</h2>
                
                <p>
                    Our specialized foundry network supplies corrosion-resistant stainless castings to:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Fluid & Flow Control:</strong>High-pressure ball valves, gate valves, pump impellers, and heavy-duty pipe fittings.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Medical & Healthcare:</strong>Surgical instruments, MRI-compatible hardware, and orthopedic device components.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Food & Beverage / Dairy:</strong>Sanitary fittings, mixing impellers, and bottling machinery parts that require strict FDA-compliant finishes.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Marine & Offshore:</strong>Saltwater-resistant cleats, shackles, propeller hubs, and subsea sensor housings (utilizing 316L and 17-4 PH).
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
</IndividualPageLayout>